<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFA16A1EFCEB94981A87BEE2" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFA16A1EFCEB94981A87BEE2" blockId="90.[790,1383,626,1053]" lastBlockId="90.[180,1390,1060,2990]" pageId="90" pageNumber="848">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFCEB94981DE9B9D0" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[791,1001,705,738]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">Eptesicus ognevi</taxonomicName>
is generally recognized as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC0694A91A6AB83B" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1018,1130,752,777]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
, but genetic data support recognition of them as distinct. Morphological data are less conclusive because 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC9395071DE8B84D" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[879,1000,862,895]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">LE. ognevi</taxonomicName>
greatly resembles 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFB0D95071B61B84D" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1265,1377,862,895]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
. Phylogenetic relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFB3D95DF1B3EB895" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[1217,1342,902,935]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC0495F41A6BB8FC" box="[1016,1131,941,974]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eptesicus</taxonomicName>
is still unresolved. Using mitochondrial genes, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFB4F958C1B2DB8C4" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[1203,1325,981,1014]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
was sister to a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFB7495A51B1CBF2F" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1160,1308,1020,1053]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
(specifically subspecies mirza and turcomanus) and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFCC0927D1DAABF77" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[828,938,1060,1093]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
, but nuclear genes showed it to be sister to a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFD9C92151D11BF5F" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[608,785,1100,1133]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hottentotus">E. hottentotus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFCDF92151DCDBF5F" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[803,973,1100,1133]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">E. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFBDD92151A92BF5F" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1057,1170,1100,1133]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
. It consistently formed a monophyletic group separate from 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFCD2922A1D9ABFA6" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[814,922,1139,1172]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
, supporting its status as a distinct species. Nevertheless, I. V. Artyushin and colleagues in 2018 found a similarly conflicting dataset that supported the traditional view that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC57929B1A1EBFD1" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[939,1054,1218,1251]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
includes 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFB50929B1B27BFD1" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[1196,1319,1218,1251]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFF4892B01F5DBE38" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[180,349,1257,1290]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">E. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
based on nuclear genes. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFD3B92B01D97BE38" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[711,919,1257,1290]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">Eptesicus ognevi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC2292B01A88BE38" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[990,1160,1257,1290]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">E. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
are included as distinct species here, pending a more complete genetic and morphological study encompassing the full distribution of all taxa in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFCD793611D98BE6B" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[811,920,1336,1369]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="EDD35797FFA16A1EFC6293611A29BE6B" box="[926,1065,1336,1369]" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Specimens in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFA16A1EFB0593611EF5BEB3" name="Afghanistan" pageId="90" pageNumber="848">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFA16A1EFEBF93391FB6BEB3" box="[323,438,1376,1409]" name="Pakistan" pageId="90" pageNumber="848">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
need to be examined further because they occur at much higher elevations than most other specimens reported for 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC7393DE1A08BE9A" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[911,1032,1415,1448]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
. Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFB0F93DE1B6BBE9A" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[1267,1387,1415,1448]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
might overlap with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFE3A93F61C6EBEE2" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[454,622,1455,1488]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">E. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
in the southern Caucasus. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFA16A1EFF4993871FFABD75" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" type="distribution">
